1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:02,794
Previously on Seducing Drake Palma.

2
00:00:03,545 --> 00:00:04,671
Next!

3
00:00:05,213 --> 00:00:06,631
Closer! A little closer, miss!

4
00:00:07,882 --> 00:00:09,050
A little more!

5
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:11,511
Come on, just a bit more!

6
00:00:14,305 --> 00:00:15,682
Like, dance with me?

7
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:18,852
Excuse me, he’s my date!

8
00:00:20,478 --> 00:00:22,272
Drake, everyone’s staring!

9
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:23,815
Don’t mind them.

10
00:00:23,845 --> 00:00:24,851
But—

11
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:40,415
Why are you dancing with me?

12
00:00:40,623 --> 00:00:42,000
Those girls are annoying.

13
00:00:42,042 --> 00:00:43,501
Am I not annoying?

14
00:00:43,877 --> 00:00:45,055
You’re annoying.

15
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:46,108
But that’s fine.

16
00:00:48,343 --> 00:00:51,289
She’s dancing with Drake,
then now with Sheen?

17
00:00:52,969 --> 00:00:55,096
I have something in mind, girls.

18
00:00:55,309 --> 00:00:56,836
Like what?

19
00:00:58,391 --> 00:00:58,892
Hey!

20
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:01,227
So, they really went through
with their plan.

21
00:01:01,562 --> 00:01:02,750
Wait! Hold on!

22
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:07,984
For your information,
I’m beautiful.

23
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:10,093
You know Drake Palma?

24
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:13,490
The arrogant and handsome guy
all the girls are chasing?

25
00:01:14,870 --> 00:01:15,997
He’s my boyfriend!

26
00:01:46,022 --> 00:01:47,941
Do you know what time it is,
Alys Zyril Perez?!

27
00:01:48,753 --> 00:01:49,825
Psst.

28
00:01:50,258 --> 00:01:51,426
What time is it?

29
00:01:52,654 --> 00:01:53,654
Tss.

30
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:56,505
6:15.

31
00:01:57,909 --> 00:02:00,013
He said it’s 6:15.

32
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:01,621
Why did you come home late?!

33
00:02:01,646 --> 00:02:03,022
We’ve been trying to reach you!

34
00:02:03,331 --> 00:02:04,911
We couldn’t sleep
worrying about you!

35
00:02:07,797 --> 00:02:09,966
Lord, guide my mother.

36
00:02:10,193 --> 00:02:12,442
Give her calmness
and providence.

37
00:02:12,467 --> 00:02:14,093
Let her see the light!

38
00:02:15,593 --> 00:02:17,428
Does a decent girl
come home in the morning?

39
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:21,307
Isn’t this better than
staying late in the evening?

40
00:02:23,663 --> 00:02:26,541
Work on it, my cuteness.

41
00:02:27,647 --> 00:02:30,233
You didn’t even notice
that you left your phone!

42
00:02:30,441 --> 00:02:32,777
We’ve been trying to reach you
all night!

43
00:02:33,329 --> 00:02:36,232
And Aya had to drop
this one off before heading home.

44
00:02:36,775 --> 00:02:37,825
What are you doing?!

45
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:40,052
Get inside!

46
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:42,490
And where do you
think you’re going?

47
00:02:44,289 --> 00:02:45,560
What’s your name, young man?

48
00:02:47,097 --> 00:02:48,107
Drake Palma.

49
00:02:49,043 --> 00:02:51,271
Okay, Mr. Palma, come inside.

50
00:02:51,546 --> 00:02:53,506
My husband and I would
like to have a word with you.

51
00:03:02,223 --> 00:03:04,419
Lord, it’s all up to you now.

52
00:03:52,482 --> 00:03:56,027
I love you, Drake Palma!

53
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:04,369
Why did you come
home just now, Alys?

54
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:09,098
Well, Mommy, I got locked
inside the stock room last night.

55
00:04:09,123 --> 00:04:10,124
But I was alone,

56
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,126
Drake was not there
with me.

57
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:13,258
Promise.

58
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:17,258
I was surprised when he
was carrying me home this morning.

59
00:04:18,383 --> 00:04:21,094
Mommy, please don’t be mad!

60
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:23,613
Is this true, Mr. Palma,

61
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:25,422
that you weren’t together
last night?

62
00:04:28,768 --> 00:04:29,805
Alys?

63
00:04:30,248 --> 00:04:31,833
Since when did
you learn how to lie?

64
00:04:32,772 --> 00:04:34,732
No, Mommy,
that’s not what happened.

65
00:04:35,024 --> 00:04:37,443
Drake, come on, tell the truth!

66
00:04:37,468 --> 00:04:39,487
You weren’t with
me last night, right?

67
00:04:44,103 --> 00:04:45,230
Uh, Hon, have a seat.

68
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:48,246
Let them talk first.

69
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:50,957
Alright, Alys, what happened?

70
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:56,004
It’s because the “like” girls
locked me in the stock room.

71
00:04:56,504 --> 00:04:57,605
Why?

72
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:59,549
Like someone’s looking for you.

73
00:05:00,174 --> 00:05:02,176
Meet me inside the stock room.

74
00:05:02,552 --> 00:05:03,586
Urgent.

75
00:05:05,471 --> 00:05:06,406
Wait, hey!

76
00:05:06,431 --> 00:05:08,933
But Drake really wasn’t with me.

77
00:05:10,977 --> 00:05:13,104
Thank you!

78
00:05:15,231 --> 00:05:18,526
Wait! Hold on!

79
00:05:20,945 --> 00:05:21,963
Pervert!

80
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:23,072
It was...

81
00:05:24,064 --> 00:05:25,148
So, who are you?

82
00:05:25,958 --> 00:05:27,126
I promise, I won’t tell.

83
00:05:27,368 --> 00:05:28,492
Pinky swear!

84
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:29,609
I’m…

85
00:05:30,669 --> 00:05:31,672
Neil?

86
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:33,166
Yeah, Neil.

87
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,460
Who’s Neil, Alys?

88
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:40,016
Our batchmate, Mommy.

89
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:43,301
Do you know this Neil, Palma?

90
00:05:45,695 --> 00:05:47,195
There’s no Neil in our batch.

91
00:05:48,514 --> 00:05:49,734
Alys!

92
00:05:50,659 --> 00:05:52,202
What did I
tell you about lying?

93
00:05:53,780 --> 00:05:56,700
Lying means no
technology for two weeks.

94
00:05:57,857 --> 00:05:58,791
Good.

95
00:05:58,816 --> 00:06:01,109
So, are you ready to tell us
what really happened last night?

96
00:06:03,652 --> 00:06:05,278
So, you want war?

97
00:06:06,154 --> 00:06:08,055
Then prepare yourself, Drake Palma!

98
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:11,726
I’m sorry for the white lie, St. Collete.

99
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:14,248
I was with Drake last night!

100
00:06:14,916 --> 00:06:16,167
And he touched me!

101
00:06:16,542 --> 00:06:17,143
What?!

102
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:18,297
She asked for it!

103
00:06:18,336 --> 00:06:18,895
Hey!

104
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,505
You’ve got some nerve!

105
00:06:21,672 --> 00:06:22,840
You’re a liar!

106
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:24,817
Hold on.

107
00:06:24,842 --> 00:06:26,677
Are you my daughter’s boyfriend, Palma?

108
00:06:27,582 --> 00:06:28,661
Drake Palma...

109
00:06:29,598 --> 00:06:31,307
You’re my boyfriend now!

110
00:06:34,228 --> 00:06:35,521
According to your daughter,

111
00:06:35,879 --> 00:06:36,880
yes sir—

112
00:06:37,254 --> 00:06:38,426
I am her boyfriend.

113
00:06:40,692 --> 00:06:42,610
She followed me one afternoon.

114
00:06:43,241 --> 00:06:45,285
She introduced herself
to my dad as my girlfriend.

115
00:06:45,819 --> 00:06:46,987
I am his girlfriend!

116
00:06:47,271 --> 00:06:49,732
I’m Alys. Alys Zyril Perez,

117
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:51,494
soon to be Palma!

118
00:06:51,702 --> 00:06:52,880
Hello!

119
00:06:52,954 --> 00:06:54,130
Actually…

120
00:06:54,163 --> 00:06:56,457
Yes, I’m really his girlfriend!

121
00:06:56,488 --> 00:06:57,823
As in girlfriend!

122
00:06:57,848 --> 00:07:00,853
As in one word, girlfriend!

123
00:07:00,878 --> 00:07:02,146
We’re really a couple!

124
00:07:02,171 --> 00:07:04,298
Right? Right, Drakey baby?

125
00:07:04,632 --> 00:07:05,716
How long have you been together?

126
00:07:06,134 --> 00:07:07,176
Five minutes?

127
00:07:11,093 --> 00:07:13,122
Princess, I didn’t think
you were like this.

128
00:07:13,699 --> 00:07:16,286
I thought you liked Sheen—and
now you’re with Drake?

129
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:21,107
Because, Dad, he doesn’t
treat me like a girlfriend!

130
00:07:21,481 --> 00:07:22,458
Hey, Drake!

131
00:07:22,483 --> 00:07:24,444
You’re only my boyfriend
in front of Sheen and Kei!

132
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:25,731
Just in front of them!

133
00:07:26,224 --> 00:07:27,583
You think I like you?

134
00:07:28,144 --> 00:07:29,896
Keep dreaming. You’re ugly.

135
00:07:31,033 --> 00:07:33,035
That’s why I forget sometimes.

136
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:35,497
Right, boyfriend?

137
00:07:36,565 --> 00:07:38,233
Because you always
hurt my feelings.

138
00:07:39,013 --> 00:07:40,101
Right, girlfriend?

139
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:41,102
Oh, so you’re talking back now?

140
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,478
Alright, that’s enough.

141
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:45,637
Drake, maybe your parents
are looking for you—go home.

142
00:07:51,569 --> 00:07:53,029
Hon, calm down.

143
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:54,765
Nothing even happened.

144
00:07:54,765 --> 00:07:56,044
They’re just teasing each other.

145
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:57,285
Puppy love!

146
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,356
Yuck, Dad!
Puppy love’s gross.

147
00:08:00,038 --> 00:08:02,082
But yes, nothing happened.

148
00:08:03,894 --> 00:08:05,209
Okay, fine.

149
00:08:05,234 --> 00:08:06,684
But you’re still grounded!

150
00:08:06,861 --> 00:08:10,406
No gadgets. And you'll stay
at home all weekend.

151
00:08:10,431 --> 00:08:11,473
Understood?

152
00:08:25,475 --> 00:08:26,497
Bestie!

153
00:08:27,193 --> 00:08:28,278
Bestie!

154
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:30,801
I missed you!

155
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:31,874
What happened?

156
00:08:31,899 --> 00:08:33,237
Was the weekend
really that long?

157
00:08:33,262 --> 00:08:34,520
Why are you clingy?

158
00:08:34,983 --> 00:08:36,776
Because I was
grounded all weekend!

159
00:08:37,378 --> 00:08:39,255
I miss you and your loud mouth!

160
00:08:39,810 --> 00:08:40,828
You’re probably just hungry!

161
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:42,063
Let’s eat, your treat!

162
00:08:42,169 --> 00:08:43,575
I’ll treat you, Bee!

163
00:08:45,769 --> 00:08:46,841
Who’s Bee?

164
00:08:47,652 --> 00:08:49,637
And why are you talking to us?

165
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:52,423
Who are you?

166
00:08:52,448 --> 00:08:53,520
You don’t know me?

167
00:08:54,158 --> 00:08:56,369
I’m the Student Council Vice President.

168
00:08:57,828 --> 00:08:58,856
Okay.

169
00:09:01,336 --> 00:09:03,714
Kent Justin Valdez, at your service.

170
00:09:04,549 --> 00:09:09,294
Do you need something,
Mr. Student Council Vice President?

171
00:09:10,007 --> 00:09:11,044
Not from you.

172
00:09:11,162 --> 00:09:13,333
But from Aya, I do.

173
00:09:14,717 --> 00:09:17,200
Bee, what’s with your face?

174
00:09:17,682 --> 00:09:19,242
Stop calling me Bee!

175
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:21,519
I’m Aya! A-ya!

176
00:09:22,144 --> 00:09:23,187
You are Bee!

177
00:09:23,604 --> 00:09:25,314
‘Cause I’m your honey!

178
00:09:27,275 --> 00:09:28,651
I’m courting Aya.

179
00:09:29,443 --> 00:09:31,571
The bee to my honey.

180
00:09:32,321 --> 00:09:33,380
Seriously?

181
00:09:33,874 --> 00:09:35,042
You’re so full of it!

182
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:36,216
Leave me alone!

183
00:09:36,771 --> 00:09:38,387
Don’t push me away, Bee.

184
00:09:38,953 --> 00:09:40,496
I’ll only fall harder!

185
00:09:40,965 --> 00:09:44,176
You’re so cute, Bee!

186
00:09:45,910 --> 00:09:49,833
Wait, why isn’t Aya
yelling or hitting Kent?

187
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:53,591
Does this mean
she likes him, too?

188
00:09:54,885 --> 00:09:56,220
So, are you hungry?

189
00:09:56,596 --> 00:09:57,606
What do you want?

190
00:09:58,431 --> 00:10:00,099
That! That one!

191
00:10:00,124 --> 00:10:01,492
That pizza! That one!

192
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:02,727
- Then that pasta!
- Pizza, pasta…

193
00:10:02,752 --> 00:10:05,505
And all the desserts! That
one too! That banana split!

194
00:10:05,660 --> 00:10:07,119
Bee, what was that again?

195
00:10:08,114 --> 00:10:09,208
Buy everything!

196
00:10:09,233 --> 00:10:11,902
Pizza, pasta, dessert!

197
00:10:12,325 --> 00:10:13,660
That Kent is so annoying!

198
00:10:14,244 --> 00:10:17,163
He’s been flooding
me with friend requests,

199
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:18,993
texts and calls,

200
00:10:19,597 --> 00:10:21,703
and now he’s bothering me
in the cafeteria, too?

201
00:10:22,993 --> 00:10:24,870
What kind of life is this?

202
00:10:27,071 --> 00:10:29,865
You finally met your match!

203
00:10:30,509 --> 00:10:31,552
That’s your karma, bestie!

204
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:36,802
Why does your karma look happy?

205
00:10:37,865 --> 00:10:39,711
Huh? What do you mean happy?

206
00:10:42,008 --> 00:10:44,761
Tada! Here you go!

207
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:48,062
Kent Justin Valdez!

208
00:10:48,439 --> 00:10:49,732
What did you do?

209
00:10:50,816 --> 00:10:52,902
Your wish is my command!

210
00:10:53,478 --> 00:10:54,771
You told me to buy everything.

211
00:10:54,796 --> 00:10:56,089
Here it is.

212
00:10:56,217 --> 00:10:57,260
Let’s eat!

213
00:10:58,908 --> 00:10:59,914
Here.

214
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:02,053
Alys, right?

215
00:11:02,078 --> 00:11:03,594
You’re Drake’s girlfriend, right?

216
00:11:04,914 --> 00:11:05,930
Why?

217
00:11:06,624 --> 00:11:08,542
Nothing.
Sheen just mentioned it.

218
00:11:09,726 --> 00:11:12,004
It seems my bestie hit the jackpot.

219
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:13,384
She got the Student
Council Vice President.

220
00:11:13,408 --> 00:11:14,811
Here comes the
choo-choo train!

221
00:11:14,836 --> 00:11:18,094
- And Kent looks cute like Sheen my loves.
- Bite a little.

222
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:20,262
- Good job, bestie!
- Good baby!

223
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:22,392
Does he know something
about Sheen and Kei?

224
00:11:22,417 --> 00:11:23,490
Here, drink some water.

225
00:11:23,515 --> 00:11:24,700
Uh, Kent!

226
00:11:24,725 --> 00:11:26,102
Are you close with Sheen?

227
00:11:26,977 --> 00:11:28,354
We’re okay. Why?

228
00:11:30,272 --> 00:11:33,150
I was just wondering if he
got back together with Kei.

229
00:11:34,318 --> 00:11:36,529
Oh, we don’t talk about that.

230
00:11:37,196 --> 00:11:38,447
I never asked either.

231
00:11:39,163 --> 00:11:40,422
- Eat up, Bee!
- Don’t pretend!

232
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,118
Looks like you’re nosy, too.

233
00:11:42,993 --> 00:11:45,329
I am not.
Only when it’s about you.

234
00:11:47,206 --> 00:11:48,328
Aya babes, eat now!

235
00:11:48,587 --> 00:11:51,006
Choo-choo train!

236
00:11:52,258 --> 00:11:53,509
Good for Aya.

237
00:11:54,309 --> 00:11:55,351
Geez.

238
00:11:55,938 --> 00:11:59,317
When will I have a real love life?

239
00:12:00,136 --> 00:12:01,211
Do you want dessert?

240
00:12:03,060 --> 00:12:04,094
[sigh]

241
00:12:04,119 --> 00:12:05,234
Or do you want hotdog again?

242
00:12:08,487 --> 00:12:09,765
There.

243
00:12:10,601 --> 00:12:11,397
Kei...

244
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:13,023
- listen to me—
- Sheen, stop it!

245
00:12:15,721 --> 00:12:17,359
Didn’t we talk about this?!

246
00:12:18,730 --> 00:12:20,391
I thought you wanted me to be happy.

247
00:12:21,323 --> 00:12:22,344
Of course, Kei.

248
00:12:23,242 --> 00:12:25,161
Then tell Alys to back off!

249
00:12:26,537 --> 00:12:27,580
Alright.

250
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:29,859
I’ll try.

251
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:41,384
Tss.

252
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:45,889
Bestie.

253
00:12:46,599 --> 00:12:47,599
Bestie.

254
00:12:48,934 --> 00:12:49,934
Bestie!

255
00:12:50,829 --> 00:12:51,829
Alys.

256
00:12:51,854 --> 00:12:52,854
Sheen.

257
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:57,568
Oh no.

258
00:12:57,943 --> 00:13:00,613
Sheen my loves still looks sad.

259
00:13:01,119 --> 00:13:02,578
He also lost weight.

260
00:13:02,823 --> 00:13:04,950
Kei has a really
strong effect on Sheen.

261
00:13:05,377 --> 00:13:07,796
It seems they haven’t
gotten back together.

262
00:13:08,245 --> 00:13:09,235
Wait.

263
00:13:09,260 --> 00:13:11,999
Does that mean there’s still
a chance for us?

264
00:13:12,541 --> 00:13:13,541
Sheen...

265
00:13:17,945 --> 00:13:18,945
Excuse me.

266
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:26,213
Wow!

267
00:13:26,646 --> 00:13:28,768
Is Drake Palma
trying to mess with me?

268
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:31,948
What right does he have to
come between me and Sheen?

269
00:13:32,394 --> 00:13:34,522
Since when did he become
an attention-seeker?

270
00:13:35,264 --> 00:13:36,264
Alys...

271
00:13:37,191 --> 00:13:38,984
Can we talk after dismissal?

272
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:40,944
Alys...

273
00:13:41,821 --> 00:13:43,096
Dad wants to see you.

274
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:45,991
I’ll see you after dismissal.

275
00:14:07,721 --> 00:14:08,848
We don’t need your

276
00:14:08,889 --> 00:14:11,058
Mission Impossible:
Seducing Drake Palma!

277
00:14:12,142 --> 00:14:14,353
You can see it
in your imagination

278
00:14:14,378 --> 00:14:15,963
that you’ve succeeded!

279
00:14:16,284 --> 00:14:19,162
Step by step, you succeeded!

280
00:14:19,845 --> 00:14:21,638
Stop it, Gabriella!

281
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:24,407
Don’t call me “Gabriella’”.
That’s gross.

282
00:14:24,432 --> 00:14:25,683
Then, shut up.

283
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:27,700
You’re talking nonsense!

284
00:14:28,872 --> 00:14:30,874
Wait, are you really going
to Uncle Steve’s later?

285
00:14:31,203 --> 00:14:32,788
What? Of course not!

286
00:14:32,813 --> 00:14:34,690
I’m going to see Sheen my loves!

287
00:14:35,185 --> 00:14:36,458
Stop talking about
that cry baby!

288
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:37,960
You’re not getting
anything from him!

289
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:39,670
Well, it’s true!

290
00:14:39,695 --> 00:14:41,196
And stop talking about Drake!

291
00:14:41,338 --> 00:14:42,064
Why?

292
00:14:42,089 --> 00:14:43,365
Just because you
have Kent now!

293
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:46,468
You’re nuts!

294
00:14:46,468 --> 00:14:47,731
- Yiee, you like Kent!
- Okay, class,

295
00:14:47,756 --> 00:14:49,424
go back to your seats!

296
00:14:57,539 --> 00:14:58,654
I wonder where he is.

297
00:15:17,848 --> 00:15:18,848
Drake.

298
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:23,672
Can we talk?

299
00:15:28,969 --> 00:15:30,054
Tss.

300
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:34,266
Chill out, brothers.

301
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:36,644
Your veins are about to pop out.

302
00:15:43,275 --> 00:15:45,110
Okay, I’m leaving now.

303
00:15:45,653 --> 00:15:47,321
Aya babes might
be looking for me.

304
00:15:47,821 --> 00:15:48,864
Just chill, okay?

305
00:15:49,195 --> 00:15:50,216
No fistfights!

306
00:15:50,613 --> 00:15:51,613
Okay?

307
00:15:53,712 --> 00:15:54,712
What?

308
00:15:57,617 --> 00:15:58,904
Did you get your assignment?

309
00:15:59,124 --> 00:16:00,124
Tss.

310
00:16:01,222 --> 00:16:02,222
Leave Alys alone.

311
00:16:05,362 --> 00:16:07,224
I’m serious.
Quit messing with my best friend.

312
00:16:11,957 --> 00:16:13,709
I don’t want.

313
00:16:16,725 --> 00:16:18,021
You don’t love her, right?

314
00:16:20,541 --> 00:16:22,418
It’s obvious how you treat her.

315
00:16:25,176 --> 00:16:28,137
Your attitude doesn’t surprise
me anymore, Drake Palma.

316
00:16:28,789 --> 00:16:30,052
I’ve known you for a long time.

317
00:16:31,865 --> 00:16:33,200
Ever since elementary,

318
00:16:33,915 --> 00:16:35,247
you only cared about yourself.

319
00:16:35,902 --> 00:16:37,450
And the worst part?

320
00:16:39,289 --> 00:16:41,041
You never cared who gets hurt.

321
00:16:42,751 --> 00:16:44,586
As long as you get
what you want.

322
00:16:46,703 --> 00:16:48,830
You’re not capable of
loving anyone, Drake.

323
00:16:53,220 --> 00:16:54,220
I might try.

324
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:00,888
I might try falling for her.

325
00:17:18,454 --> 00:17:19,830
- What’s taking him so long?
- Oops, sorry!

326
00:17:19,855 --> 00:17:21,599
Where are you going, Bee?
Should I stay here?

327
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:23,536
Where are you staying?

328
00:17:23,823 --> 00:17:25,091
- Come on.
- I’ll stay here.

329
00:17:25,711 --> 00:17:26,833
What now, Aya?

330
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:28,839
I’m going to see Sheen!

331
00:17:29,965 --> 00:17:31,107
This is frustrating.

332
00:17:31,258 --> 00:17:32,634
Relax, bestie!

333
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:36,346
Drake is taking too long!

334
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:39,475
Are you sure you saw
Sheen and Drake talking?

335
00:17:39,975 --> 00:17:41,101
Yes, I saw them.

336
00:17:41,747 --> 00:17:42,999
But maybe it’s over by now.

337
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:45,414
It’s taking so long!

338
00:17:45,439 --> 00:17:46,815
My bag is so heavy!

339
00:17:50,591 --> 00:17:51,607
Catch!

340
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:54,646
Wow, that was a hard throw, Bee!

341
00:17:54,941 --> 00:17:56,609
You’re abusing my feelings!

342
00:17:57,542 --> 00:18:00,128
You want to know my
definition of abuse?

343
00:18:01,205 --> 00:18:02,414
- Mhm.
- Good!

344
00:18:02,831 --> 00:18:04,458
- You asked for this, didn’t you?
- Mhm.

345
00:18:04,483 --> 00:18:06,419
- So deal with it.
- Yes, ma’am!

346
00:18:09,463 --> 00:18:10,564
Drake!

347
00:18:10,589 --> 00:18:12,466
Come here, hurry!

348
00:18:17,945 --> 00:18:19,865
- There you go.
- Ouch, Aya!

349
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:22,810
Since Drake’s here, we’re leaving.

350
00:18:23,393 --> 00:18:25,354
Go, DraLys! Bye!

351
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:26,747
“We?”

352
00:18:26,772 --> 00:18:27,689
You mean “us”?

353
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:29,775
Come on, Bee!

354
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:32,386
I know those moves!

355
00:18:33,028 --> 00:18:33,879
Where are we going?

356
00:18:33,904 --> 00:18:34,982
Is this a date?

357
00:18:35,614 --> 00:18:37,068
You know what,
they actually look cute together.

358
00:18:37,093 --> 00:18:38,115
Like us.

359
00:18:38,598 --> 00:18:40,654
So if they’re
“DraLys,” what are we?

360
00:18:44,164 --> 00:18:45,432
“KenYa?”

361
00:18:45,457 --> 00:18:47,167
Can yah go on a date with me?

362
00:18:47,192 --> 00:18:48,779
What “KenYa” are you talking about?!

363
00:18:49,086 --> 00:18:50,865
Date your butt, I’m going home!

364
00:18:51,088 --> 00:18:52,631
Bee, wait! Alys!

365
00:18:53,173 --> 00:18:55,076
I’m coming!
Introduce me to your parents!

366
00:18:55,101 --> 00:18:56,311
Wait, Bee!

367
00:18:58,972 --> 00:18:59,997
Bee, come on!

368
00:19:00,472 --> 00:19:01,943
- Wait up! I’m coming!
- You’re annoying!

369
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:03,990
- You’re relentless!
- I’m coming with you!

370
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:05,227
Leave me alone.

371
00:19:05,252 --> 00:19:06,837
This is perfect, I’m finally
meeting your parents!

372
00:19:07,062 --> 00:19:08,205
Meet your face.

373
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:09,404
Future mother-in-law,

374
00:19:09,429 --> 00:19:11,216
future father-in-law! Right?

375
00:19:11,241 --> 00:19:12,950
Bestie’s doing a good job.

376
00:19:13,151 --> 00:19:15,724
She charmed the playboy
of St. Collete High.

377
00:19:16,083 --> 00:19:19,908
While I’m stuck with this
annoying jerk.

378
00:19:20,057 --> 00:19:21,099
It’s frustrating.

379
00:19:21,568 --> 00:19:23,069
I’ll just go to Sheen.

380
00:19:24,186 --> 00:19:26,263
Ouch! Let go of me!

381
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:28,338
I’m still mad at you!

382
00:19:28,599 --> 00:19:30,561
I got grounded the entire
weekend because of you

383
00:19:30,586 --> 00:19:31,628
and your nonsense!

384
00:19:31,946 --> 00:19:32,946
Tss.

385
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:36,362
Ouch! Let me go!

386
00:19:36,430 --> 00:19:37,443
Noisy.

387
00:19:38,753 --> 00:19:40,028
I said let go!

388
00:19:40,053 --> 00:19:42,055
I’m going to see Sheen! What?!

389
00:19:45,932 --> 00:19:47,100
What?

390
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:48,376
You got a problem?

391
00:19:53,942 --> 00:19:55,152
You’re my girlfriend.

392
00:19:56,862 --> 00:20:00,122
Act like one.

393
00:20:11,793 --> 00:20:12,961
Maybe I should just go home.

394
00:20:13,516 --> 00:20:15,344
- This is so embarrassing.
- Alys, Drake!

395
00:20:18,159 --> 00:20:21,261
Oh no, Uncle Steve saw me.

396
00:20:21,803 --> 00:20:23,931
There’s no backing out now.

397
00:20:24,348 --> 00:20:27,184
Perfect timing! Your Aunt Katrina and I
brought something for you.

398
00:20:27,559 --> 00:20:29,534
Oh no. About that, too.

399
00:20:31,232 --> 00:20:32,456
Time to eat.

400
00:20:34,198 --> 00:20:35,284
Give me that!

401
00:20:37,699 --> 00:20:40,660
I’m not ready to see Aunt Katrina yet.

402
00:20:41,112 --> 00:20:44,743
The last time I saw her,
I was sitting on Drake’s bed

403
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:48,413
with three inches distance
of our faces.

404
00:20:48,413 --> 00:20:49,539
What am I going to do?

405
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:51,833
Alys? Alys?

406
00:20:53,105 --> 00:20:54,231
Thank you, Uncle!

407
00:20:54,544 --> 00:20:56,296
Is Aunt Katrina inside?

408
00:20:56,672 --> 00:20:57,773
She left this morning.

409
00:20:57,798 --> 00:20:59,383
She needs to do something
for the wedding.

410
00:20:59,898 --> 00:21:01,557
What a relief.

411
00:21:01,620 --> 00:21:03,637
It’s good she’s not here!

412
00:21:04,559 --> 00:21:05,685
Is that so?

413
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:08,558
Too bad I didn’t get to say hi but…

414
00:21:09,142 --> 00:21:10,435
maybe next time.

415
00:21:10,643 --> 00:21:12,979
That’s okay.
There’ll be another chance!

416
00:21:13,772 --> 00:21:14,838
Let’s go inside.

417
00:21:16,772 --> 00:21:17,856
Look at him.

418
00:21:18,203 --> 00:21:21,588
After saying “You’re my girlfriend.
Act like one.”,

419
00:21:21,761 --> 00:21:23,799
he’s leaving me out here?

420
00:21:23,824 --> 00:21:24,824
What a jerk.

421
00:21:25,379 --> 00:21:26,379
Let’s go, Alys!

422
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:27,702
Alright, Uncle.

423
00:21:33,849 --> 00:21:35,642
Bee, wait up!

424
00:21:38,060 --> 00:21:39,060
Bee, wait!

425
00:21:39,547 --> 00:21:40,547
It’s hot out here.

426
00:21:40,609 --> 00:21:41,609
Here.

427
00:21:42,326 --> 00:21:43,326
Are you okay?

428
00:21:44,207 --> 00:21:45,207
Bee, hold on!

429
00:21:46,904 --> 00:21:47,904
Bee!

430
00:21:47,958 --> 00:21:48,990
Just a sec!

431
00:21:49,645 --> 00:21:50,645
Sorry.

432
00:21:54,780 --> 00:21:56,490
Bee! Bee!

433
00:21:57,241 --> 00:21:58,592
Bee, wait up!

434
00:21:58,617 --> 00:21:59,827
Wait for me! Wait!

435
00:22:00,953 --> 00:22:02,371
Uh, sorry, sorry!

436
00:22:03,658 --> 00:22:04,755
Bee, come on!

437
00:22:06,293 --> 00:22:07,380
Bee, wait...

438
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:11,029
Bee, wait up!

439
00:22:16,969 --> 00:22:18,095
Bee, are you tired?

440
00:22:18,804 --> 00:22:21,265
Here, go to sleep.

441
00:22:21,682 --> 00:22:22,808
I’ll wake you up later.

442
00:22:24,588 --> 00:22:25,771
Am I a kinder student?

443
00:22:26,233 --> 00:22:27,333
Who has nap time?

444
00:22:28,365 --> 00:22:30,242
Well, you said you
were tired earlier.

445
00:22:30,399 --> 00:22:31,650
Sorry, Bee.

446
00:22:35,237 --> 00:22:36,732
Thank you!

447
00:22:36,822 --> 00:22:38,324
So pretty!

448
00:22:38,490 --> 00:22:39,633
It’s looks good on you!

449
00:22:39,658 --> 00:22:41,118
Try this one, try it on!

450
00:22:42,619 --> 00:22:44,079
It fits you!

451
00:22:44,538 --> 00:22:46,165
You and your
girlfriend really match!

452
00:22:46,190 --> 00:22:47,190
Tss.

453
00:22:47,630 --> 00:22:48,917
You’re a match.

454
00:22:49,793 --> 00:22:51,211
Uh, Uncle Steve,

455
00:22:51,337 --> 00:22:53,172
why did you want
to see me again?

456
00:22:53,839 --> 00:22:55,674
What?
Who said I was looking for you?

457
00:22:56,901 --> 00:22:57,896
Tss. Wedding.

458
00:22:58,677 --> 00:22:59,677
Oh no.

459
00:22:59,762 --> 00:23:00,904
Uncle Steve!

460
00:23:01,221 --> 00:23:03,032
I’m way too young
to get married!

461
00:23:03,057 --> 00:23:05,809
And your son hasn’t
even proposed to me yet!

462
00:23:06,393 --> 00:23:10,105
And if this is about
that thing he said,

463
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:11,927
that I forced him to touch me—

464
00:23:11,982 --> 00:23:15,027
I swear I won’t press
charges! Promise!

465
00:23:15,085 --> 00:23:17,629
Uncle Steve, please,
we can’t get married yet.

466
00:23:17,654 --> 00:23:20,407
Please, Uncle Steve!

467
00:23:21,283 --> 00:23:24,036
Alys, come on..
That’s not what Drake meant.

468
00:23:24,495 --> 00:23:27,075
He was talking about
Katrina’s and my wedding.

469
00:23:29,666 --> 00:23:32,568
Of course, Uncle Steve,
I was just joking!

470
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:37,168
Obviously, I knew you were
talking about your wedding!

471
00:23:37,966 --> 00:23:39,740
But wait, what exactly

472
00:23:40,052 --> 00:23:41,470
is Drake accusing you of?

473
00:23:41,495 --> 00:23:42,495
- Huh?
- What are you saying?

474
00:23:43,408 --> 00:23:44,909
We were together last night.

475
00:23:45,766 --> 00:23:47,200
He touched me.

476
00:23:47,393 --> 00:23:48,700
- What?!
- She asked for it!

477
00:23:49,186 --> 00:23:51,552
Hey! You’ve got some nerve!

478
00:23:52,449 --> 00:23:53,617
You’re a liar!

479
00:23:59,863 --> 00:24:01,865
Oh no, Uncle, just ignore me.

480
00:24:01,907 --> 00:24:03,325
I was just saying nonsense.

481
00:24:03,367 --> 00:24:06,286
It’s nothing.
Please forget I said that.

482
00:24:09,164 --> 00:24:10,791
Drake, where are you going?

483
00:24:14,378 --> 00:24:17,047
Alys, why don’t you
have some snacks first?

484
00:24:24,179 --> 00:24:25,681
Thank you, Uncle!

485
00:24:29,369 --> 00:24:30,936
- Kent.
- Yes, Bee?

486
00:24:31,770 --> 00:24:33,772
Aya. My name is Aya.

487
00:24:35,536 --> 00:24:36,537
I’m serious—

488
00:24:38,402 --> 00:24:39,445
stop bothering me.

489
00:24:40,320 --> 00:24:41,530
I’m serious too, Aya.

490
00:24:41,905 --> 00:24:43,240
I’m not going to stop.

491
00:24:43,615 --> 00:24:44,615
But why?

492
00:24:45,909 --> 00:24:46,909
Why me?

493
00:24:48,036 --> 00:24:49,121
Why don’t you believe me?

494
00:24:54,084 --> 00:24:55,544
I like you, Bee.

495
00:24:56,712 --> 00:24:57,963
I’ll do anything for you.

496
00:24:59,465 --> 00:25:00,466
Isn’t it obvious?

497
00:25:01,383 --> 00:25:02,801
You treat me like a slave.

498
00:25:04,490 --> 00:25:06,117
I like you, Bee!

499
00:25:07,598 --> 00:25:08,849
Why are you yelling?!

500
00:25:08,874 --> 00:25:11,046
Bee, please!

501
00:25:13,645 --> 00:25:14,741
Please?

502
00:25:19,818 --> 00:25:21,256
Thank you again, Uncle Steve.

503
00:25:21,487 --> 00:25:23,197
Do you need anything else from me?

504
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:24,341
For the wedding?

505
00:25:25,073 --> 00:25:25,757
Yes, Alys.

506
00:25:25,782 --> 00:25:27,618
Did anyone tell you you’re
part of the entourage?

507
00:25:27,910 --> 00:25:28,991
Really, Uncle?

508
00:25:30,078 --> 00:25:31,955
It means I will be wearing a gown?

509
00:25:32,372 --> 00:25:33,335
Mmm-hmm!

510
00:25:34,082 --> 00:25:36,210
I’ll just tell Drake
to bring you here

511
00:25:36,627 --> 00:25:39,129
for the gown fitting and
and rehearsals.

512
00:25:41,423 --> 00:25:44,259
Wait, did Drake tell you
he switched sections?

513
00:25:45,594 --> 00:25:46,594
What?

514
00:25:53,208 --> 00:25:54,208
I wonder where he is now.

515
00:25:55,592 --> 00:25:56,592
You didn’t know?

516
00:25:57,014 --> 00:25:58,933
A girlfriend should be the one
to know first.

517
00:25:58,982 --> 00:25:59,982
Why didn’t you know?

518
00:26:00,943 --> 00:26:02,694
Uh…um…

519
00:26:02,719 --> 00:26:04,338
he didn’t really mention it.

520
00:26:04,363 --> 00:26:05,656
He hasn’t said anything to me.

521
00:26:06,323 --> 00:26:07,699
But why did he switch?

522
00:26:08,158 --> 00:26:11,620
From what I know, it’s
because of his high grades.

523
00:26:12,162 --> 00:26:13,247
Oh, I see.

524
00:26:13,830 --> 00:26:15,541
How about you, Alys?
What’s your average?

525
00:26:19,127 --> 00:26:21,561
It’s okay. It’s fine!

526
00:26:24,299 --> 00:26:25,889
Hold on, Alys.
I need to take this call.

527
00:26:37,604 --> 00:26:38,604
Where could he be?

528
00:26:39,523 --> 00:26:40,774
Should I just go home?

529
00:26:43,657 --> 00:26:45,414
I knew I shouldn’t have come here!

530
00:26:57,848 --> 00:27:00,684
But sometimes it’s hard to stay mad.

531
00:27:02,172 --> 00:27:05,467
How are you supposed to stay mad
at someone that good-looking?

532
00:27:05,875 --> 00:27:08,805
Mind you, he’s just wearing house clothes.

533
00:27:09,725 --> 00:27:11,143
Oh my.

534
00:27:12,425 --> 00:27:15,261
It’s the Drake Palma Way.

535
00:27:38,457 --> 00:27:39,457
Hey!

536
00:27:40,751 --> 00:27:42,294
You switched sections?

537
00:27:43,128 --> 00:27:45,631
What about our business report?

538
00:27:48,216 --> 00:27:49,216
Print it.

539
00:27:49,801 --> 00:27:53,055
Nice! So waiting this
long wasn’t a total waste!

540
00:27:53,242 --> 00:27:54,243
Anyway,

541
00:27:54,268 --> 00:27:55,311
I’ll head out.

542
00:27:55,656 --> 00:27:58,116
Tell Uncle Steve thanks for this!

543
00:27:58,393 --> 00:27:59,286
It’s cute!

544
00:27:59,311 --> 00:28:00,687
Thanks again! Bye!

545
00:28:03,815 --> 00:28:04,815
What?

546
00:28:06,088 --> 00:28:07,088
Tutorials.

547
00:28:08,904 --> 00:28:09,904
Forget it.

548
00:28:10,197 --> 00:28:11,664
I’m not in the mood to study.

549
00:28:12,115 --> 00:28:13,156
Tss.

550
00:28:14,451 --> 00:28:15,451
Bird brain!

551
00:28:17,454 --> 00:28:18,497
You’re rude!

552
00:28:19,289 --> 00:28:20,749
Did you just call me bird brain?

553
00:28:20,916 --> 00:28:21,916
Why?

554
00:28:22,549 --> 00:28:23,549
It’s obvious, right?

555
00:28:26,296 --> 00:28:27,631
Remember this.

556
00:28:29,049 --> 00:28:32,552
Next quarter,
I’m transferring to your section.

557
00:28:32,552 --> 00:28:33,601
Not with that

558
00:28:34,346 --> 00:28:36,431
bird brain headband.

559
00:28:38,975 --> 00:28:40,852
Whatever, I’m out of here.
I’m going home.

560
00:28:58,578 --> 00:28:59,746
Alys.

561
00:29:02,541 --> 00:29:06,336
Wow, being grounded

562
00:29:06,378 --> 00:29:08,338
lets you catch up on reading!

563
00:29:13,719 --> 00:29:17,139
Anyway, I’m lifting
your punishment.

564
00:29:17,347 --> 00:29:18,687
You’re no longer grounded.

565
00:29:19,224 --> 00:29:20,267
Really, Mom?

566
00:29:21,393 --> 00:29:22,769
Thank you, Mom!

567
00:29:22,978 --> 00:29:26,732
You know we don’t
like it when you lie.

568
00:29:27,357 --> 00:29:28,208
Right?

569
00:29:28,233 --> 00:29:30,242
It’s okay to have a boyfriend—

570
00:29:30,569 --> 00:29:32,305
as long as you focus on school.

571
00:29:33,155 --> 00:29:36,074
We have a dream, right?
From St. Collete High,

572
00:29:36,533 --> 00:29:39,161
you have to make it
into St. Collete Academy.

573
00:29:39,369 --> 00:29:42,164
So how’s that going to happen
if you don’t do your best?

574
00:29:43,832 --> 00:29:45,167
Sorry, mom.

575
00:29:45,500 --> 00:29:46,918
I know you’re sorry,

576
00:29:47,085 --> 00:29:48,755
but you have to try harder.

577
00:29:49,379 --> 00:29:53,049
Do you want to follow your sibling to
the U.S. just to get your act together?

578
00:29:54,342 --> 00:29:55,844
So try harder.

579
00:29:56,094 --> 00:29:58,513
I know you can do it.

580
00:30:01,388 --> 00:30:02,555
Don’t worry, Mom!

581
00:30:03,059 --> 00:30:05,353
I’ll work on getting my grades up!

582
00:30:05,645 --> 00:30:07,898
I’ll get into St.
Collete Academy,

583
00:30:08,064 --> 00:30:09,615
because I’m not a bird brain!

584
00:30:10,817 --> 00:30:13,320
Of course not!
Who said you were a bird brain?

585
00:30:19,121 --> 00:30:20,130
Bird brain.

586
00:30:22,913 --> 00:30:24,014
No one.

587
00:30:24,039 --> 00:30:25,182
Anyway, Mom,

588
00:30:25,207 --> 00:30:26,583
I’ll make you proud!

589
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,001
That’s my girl!

590
00:30:29,211 --> 00:30:31,087
I love you so much, Mom!

591
00:30:40,180 --> 00:30:42,599
But don’t forget to study, okay?

592
00:30:42,789 --> 00:30:43,825
Just chill.

593
00:30:43,850 --> 00:30:46,686
Alys, are your grades
worth celebrating?

594
00:30:48,063 --> 00:30:50,065
I think they’re fine, Mom.

595
00:30:51,149 --> 00:30:54,586
Well, make sure
that “fine” and “I think”

596
00:30:54,611 --> 00:30:57,823
can get you into a good
college—if not the best!

597
00:30:58,073 --> 00:31:00,951
Alys, you know the dream, right?

598
00:31:01,326 --> 00:31:04,162
You need to get into
St. Collete Academy.

599
00:31:04,412 --> 00:31:06,122
- Yes?
- Yes, Mom.

600
00:31:10,627 --> 00:31:12,712
Hey! Classmate!

601
00:31:13,004 --> 00:31:14,047
Hey. How are you?

602
00:31:20,672 --> 00:31:21,818
Oh.

603
00:31:25,264 --> 00:31:27,193
A miracle’s happening!

604
00:31:27,227 --> 00:31:28,552
Is it a crime to study now?

605
00:31:28,913 --> 00:31:31,184
Just because I touched a
book, it’s already a miracle?

606
00:31:32,107 --> 00:31:33,400
Sorry, bestie!

607
00:31:33,817 --> 00:31:35,151
Why are you so cranky?

608
00:31:36,194 --> 00:31:37,320
What are you studying?

609
00:31:39,364 --> 00:31:40,364
Here.

610
00:31:41,684 --> 00:31:42,684
Let’s study!

611
00:31:45,537 --> 00:31:46,537
No, thanks.

612
00:31:47,163 --> 00:31:48,482
I’m happy with
what I already know.

613
00:31:50,333 --> 00:31:52,961
Why are you suddenly
into studying, anyway?

614
00:31:53,503 --> 00:31:54,813
Is it end of the world?

615
00:31:54,838 --> 00:31:55,838
Sshh!

616
00:31:56,456 --> 00:31:57,456
Just be quiet!

617
00:31:58,377 --> 00:31:59,377
I need to focus!

618
00:32:00,510 --> 00:32:01,510
Alright, fine!

619
00:32:01,535 --> 00:32:02,771
Then, focus.

620
00:32:08,143 --> 00:32:09,677
Wow, you’re tired already?

621
00:32:09,702 --> 00:32:10,871
Shut up!

622
00:32:10,896 --> 00:32:12,664
- I just remembered something!
- What is it?

623
00:32:12,689 --> 00:32:14,333
We’re bridesmaids for
Aunt Katrina’s wedding!

624
00:32:18,874 --> 00:32:19,896
Gross!

625
00:32:20,655 --> 00:32:22,799
I don’t want to be part of that

626
00:32:22,824 --> 00:32:24,263
cradle snatcher’s wedding!

627
00:32:24,993 --> 00:32:27,078
Over my dead body!

628
00:32:27,454 --> 00:32:28,597
You’re harsh.

629
00:32:28,622 --> 00:32:30,255
It’s still Uncle Steve’s wedding.

630
00:32:31,082 --> 00:32:34,310
After everything he’s done for us?

631
00:32:38,715 --> 00:32:39,715
I hate this.

632
00:32:41,051 --> 00:32:42,051
Fine!

633
00:32:42,177 --> 00:32:43,177
I’ll think about it.

634
00:32:57,752 --> 00:32:59,921
[bell rings]

635
00:33:01,071 --> 00:33:02,197
Okay, class.

636
00:33:03,239 --> 00:33:05,408
Please stay if you have
tutorial sessions.

637
00:33:09,371 --> 00:33:10,371
Ugh!

638
00:33:10,997 --> 00:33:13,229
I thought today was
a Drake-free day!

639
00:33:17,170 --> 00:33:18,713
Why do you look so happy?

640
00:33:19,881 --> 00:33:21,925
Because there’s a tutorial.

641
00:33:22,550 --> 00:33:24,909
That means I won’t see Kent today.

642
00:33:25,595 --> 00:33:26,846
Then, good for you!

643
00:33:27,472 --> 00:33:28,515
I’ll go and see Drake.

644
00:33:29,215 --> 00:33:30,215
Good luck, bestie!

645
00:33:30,976 --> 00:33:31,976
Aja!

646
00:33:32,002 --> 00:33:33,002
Aja.

647
00:33:34,896 --> 00:33:35,896
One more.

648
00:33:36,481 --> 00:33:37,481
Aja!

649
00:33:38,191 --> 00:33:39,191
Aja.

650
00:33:46,449 --> 00:33:47,617
Okay.

651
00:33:56,835 --> 00:33:58,211
Uh, Sheen.

652
00:33:58,461 --> 00:33:59,461
What?

653
00:34:01,506 --> 00:34:02,716
- Let me be the one to—
- What happened to you?

654
00:34:02,716 --> 00:34:04,009
—tutor Aya babes, please!

655
00:34:04,384 --> 00:34:06,138
Hold on, I’m fixing my things!

656
00:34:06,302 --> 00:34:08,680
Let me be her tutor—
she needs me!

657
00:34:09,639 --> 00:34:10,639
Fine!

658
00:34:11,349 --> 00:34:13,435
Just tell Mr. de Juan
that you’re taking over, okay?

659
00:34:13,460 --> 00:34:14,732
Okay!

660
00:34:14,757 --> 00:34:16,096
Thank you, bro! I owe you one!

661
00:34:16,121 --> 00:34:17,372
Thank you.

662
00:34:29,507 --> 00:34:30,507
Drake!

663
00:34:32,454 --> 00:34:33,454
What?

664
00:34:33,830 --> 00:34:34,873
Let me tutor Alys.

665
00:34:36,458 --> 00:34:37,500
Tss.

666
00:34:38,138 --> 00:34:39,514
Drake, are you okay with that?

667
00:34:46,217 --> 00:34:47,224
No.

668
00:34:48,762 --> 00:34:49,762
Why not?

669
00:34:50,764 --> 00:34:52,271
You don’t even like Alys, right?

670
00:34:53,725 --> 00:34:54,725
Why?

671
00:34:55,226 --> 00:34:56,519
Who’s smarter between us?

672
00:34:57,228 --> 00:34:58,228
Hmm?

673
00:35:04,319 --> 00:35:05,737
If you make Alys cry,

674
00:35:06,946 --> 00:35:07,946
you better hide.

675
00:35:10,366 --> 00:35:11,493
Where is that CB?

676
00:35:13,119 --> 00:35:14,496
Why is he making me wait?

677
00:35:15,288 --> 00:35:18,124
He didn’t even call or text.

678
00:35:18,629 --> 00:35:19,629
He’s so annoying!

679
00:35:22,212 --> 00:35:23,271
Hi, Bee!

680
00:35:23,296 --> 00:35:25,440
Why is this
liitle pest here again?

681
00:35:25,465 --> 00:35:28,593
I thought today was
Kent-Justin-Valdez-free day, too.

682
00:35:29,173 --> 00:35:31,912
Hello, the honey to my bee!

683
00:35:33,515 --> 00:35:35,116
What are you doing?

684
00:35:35,735 --> 00:35:37,405
Snacks. For you!

685
00:35:39,129 --> 00:35:40,130
Here you go!

686
00:35:44,192 --> 00:35:45,568
Where’s Sheen?

687
00:35:46,136 --> 00:35:47,169
Sheen’s not here.

688
00:35:47,570 --> 00:35:48,599
Cover your eyes.

689
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:50,490
This is for you!

690
00:35:52,659 --> 00:35:53,660
Where’s Sheen?

691
00:35:54,327 --> 00:35:56,107
I told you, he’s not here!

692
00:35:56,204 --> 00:35:57,330
Starting today,

693
00:35:57,539 --> 00:35:58,790
I’ll be your tutor.

694
00:35:58,957 --> 00:36:00,169
Why you?!

695
00:36:01,292 --> 00:36:03,711
Bee, lower your voice.

696
00:36:04,379 --> 00:36:07,257
It should be me,
so we can have quality time.

697
00:36:07,423 --> 00:36:08,399
Right?

698
00:36:08,424 --> 00:36:10,652
My gosh! Shame on you, Kent!

699
00:36:10,677 --> 00:36:12,357
Why should I be
ashamed of my feelings?

700
00:36:13,012 --> 00:36:14,305
You’re so gross!

701
00:36:14,806 --> 00:36:15,841
Love you too, Bee!

702
00:36:16,891 --> 00:36:17,958
Okay!

703
00:36:18,309 --> 00:36:19,477
Where do you want to start?

704
00:36:27,067 --> 00:36:28,067
Nice!

705
00:36:29,529 --> 00:36:30,740
What’s with the face?

706
00:36:30,780 --> 00:36:31,780
Huh?

707
00:36:31,906 --> 00:36:33,992
You’re happy my score is low?

708
00:36:34,951 --> 00:36:35,951
Nothing.

709
00:36:36,703 --> 00:36:37,703
What is it?

710
00:36:38,860 --> 00:36:41,015
Mr. de Juan said

711
00:36:41,040 --> 00:36:42,917
we can extend tutorials
over the weekend

712
00:36:42,959 --> 00:36:44,919
if your grades are that bad!

713
00:36:46,034 --> 00:36:48,131
And your grades
are that bad, Bee!

714
00:36:48,597 --> 00:36:49,815
Nice!

715
00:36:49,841 --> 00:36:51,612
Weekends with Bee!

716
00:36:53,278 --> 00:36:54,571
- Aya, what are you doing?!
- Let’s start.

717
00:36:54,596 --> 00:36:55,805
Back to Chapter Four.

718
00:36:55,901 --> 00:36:56,973
Read this first.

719
00:36:56,998 --> 00:36:58,416
Read the instructions carefully.

720
00:37:06,941 --> 00:37:07,400
Hey,

721
00:37:08,067 --> 00:37:09,068
aren’t you going to teach me?

722
00:37:09,485 --> 00:37:11,112
I’ve been sitting
here at the library

723
00:37:11,112 --> 00:37:12,780
and you’re not even helping me!

724
00:37:13,198 --> 00:37:14,198
Tss.

725
00:37:14,949 --> 00:37:15,949
Why would I?

726
00:37:17,035 --> 00:37:18,035
Look at you.

727
00:37:19,078 --> 00:37:20,747
Who’s really the
dummy between us?

728
00:37:21,497 --> 00:37:22,790
You’re my tutor, remember?

729
00:37:23,958 --> 00:37:24,958
Tss.

730
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:27,920
Hey!

731
00:37:30,423 --> 00:37:31,758
I don’t want to teach you.

732
00:37:32,993 --> 00:37:35,120
Fine, don’t! I’ll report you to sir!

733
00:37:44,437 --> 00:37:45,437
Fine!

734
00:37:50,985 --> 00:37:55,006
Break even point or
BEP is calculated by

735
00:37:55,031 --> 00:37:58,326
dividing fixed
costs by contribution

736
00:37:58,576 --> 00:37:59,911
margin per unit.

737
00:38:01,537 --> 00:38:04,499
Selling price or SP
minus variable cost

738
00:38:04,524 --> 00:38:07,027
or VC equals
contribution margin.

739
00:38:08,336 --> 00:38:09,336
So,

740
00:38:10,213 --> 00:38:13,800
BEP equals fixed costs

741
00:38:14,259 --> 00:38:16,861
divided by selling price,

742
00:38:16,886 --> 00:38:19,222
minus variable cost per unit.

743
00:38:20,014 --> 00:38:21,014
Ugh!

744
00:38:24,894 --> 00:38:26,771
Why are you staring at me?

745
00:38:29,524 --> 00:38:30,781
Alright, fine. I’ll teach you.

746
00:38:31,359 --> 00:38:32,014
Nice!

747
00:38:32,039 --> 00:38:33,832
See, I knew you’d
give in eventually!

748
00:38:33,987 --> 00:38:34,879
Finally.

749
00:38:34,904 --> 00:38:36,320
- I really can’t do this alone.
- But…

750
00:38:37,115 --> 00:38:38,658
What’s the condition?

751
00:38:39,826 --> 00:38:40,826
But what?

752
00:38:46,207 --> 00:38:47,207
Kiss me.

753
00:38:49,585 --> 00:38:51,504
What kind of drama is
this, Drake Palma?!

754
00:38:51,529 --> 00:38:52,880
- Sssh!
- Ssshhh!

755
00:38:54,257 --> 00:38:57,051
Why are you always shouting?
We’re in the library!

756
00:38:57,885 --> 00:38:58,845
How can I not shout?

757
00:38:58,845 --> 00:39:00,664
You’re saying you want to kiss me here?

758
00:39:05,435 --> 00:39:06,494
Kiss you?

759
00:39:06,519 --> 00:39:08,375
In your dreams, Drake Palma!

760
00:39:11,524 --> 00:39:12,625
You know what,

761
00:39:12,650 --> 00:39:14,062
if you want a kiss,

762
00:39:14,444 --> 00:39:15,903
go to your Katrina!

763
00:39:20,450 --> 00:39:21,450
Drake.

764
00:40:03,034 --> 00:40:04,034
Drake.

765
00:40:04,660 --> 00:40:05,660
What?

766
00:40:06,289 --> 00:40:07,373
Let me tutor Alys.

767
00:40:08,831 --> 00:40:10,203
Drake, are you okay with it?

768
00:40:16,370 --> 00:40:17,370
No.

769
00:40:17,908 --> 00:40:18,908
Why not?

770
00:40:19,773 --> 00:40:21,024
You don’t even like Alys, right?

771
00:40:21,541 --> 00:40:22,541
Why?

772
00:40:23,846 --> 00:40:25,250
Who’s smarter between us?

773
00:40:26,724 --> 00:40:27,724
Right?

774
00:40:34,836 --> 00:40:36,172
If you make Alys cry,

775
00:40:37,485 --> 00:40:38,609
you better hide.

776
00:40:39,278 --> 00:40:41,609
I know that you’re only
doing this for Kei.

777
00:40:42,407 --> 00:40:43,883
You’re only going to hurt Alys.

778
00:40:44,272 --> 00:40:45,812
I don’t want you to hurt her.

779
00:40:54,335 --> 00:40:57,505
On the next episode of
Seducing Drake Palma.

780
00:40:59,173 --> 00:41:00,242
Hey, Drake.

781
00:41:00,550 --> 00:41:01,726
Do we…

782
00:41:02,097 --> 00:41:03,319
Do we have a monthsary?

783
00:41:04,145 --> 00:41:05,145
Tss.

784
00:41:05,388 --> 00:41:06,388
Come on, let’s go.

785
00:41:07,045 --> 00:41:09,805
I said I’m tired,
Drake Sebastian Palma.

786
00:41:13,771 --> 00:41:14,771
Hop on.

787
00:41:26,284 --> 00:41:27,535
I know!

788
00:41:27,785 --> 00:41:29,829
Let’s just say we got
together on September 31!

789
00:41:30,126 --> 00:41:31,126
Stupid.

790
00:41:31,747 --> 00:41:33,391
There’s no such
thing as September 31.

791
00:41:33,416 --> 00:41:34,267
Enjoy your special day.

792
00:41:34,292 --> 00:41:35,460
- Alright, go ahead!
- Happy monthsary!

793
00:41:35,501 --> 00:41:36,501
Enjoy!

794
00:41:36,919 --> 00:41:37,920
- But, Uncle!
- Wait!

795
00:41:41,132 --> 00:41:42,132
Oopps!

796
00:41:42,157 --> 00:41:43,157
Oopps!

797
00:41:43,593 --> 00:41:44,594
Oh, sorry!

798
00:41:45,219 --> 00:41:46,846
I didn’t mean to!

799
00:41:47,889 --> 00:41:49,407
You know what would
work best right now?

800
00:41:49,432 --> 00:41:51,094
Just take your clothes off!

801
00:41:56,230 --> 00:41:58,148
Can you still handle
the heat, bestie?

802
00:41:59,609 --> 00:42:00,812
Do you want some juice?

803
00:42:01,766 --> 00:42:04,864
Let’s just celebrate every 31st,

804
00:42:04,889 --> 00:42:07,225
so we only have to do it
seven times a year, okay?

805
00:42:08,117 --> 00:42:10,039
You really think we’d last a year?
Dream on!

806
00:42:12,997 --> 00:42:14,914
Who says that I’m gonna
break up with you?
